[{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"# Pre-Processing Data\n\nThis notebook is a continuation meant to be viewed after the Data Exploration notebook. In this notebook we will address some of the issues we've identified in our data exploration for ML model development. We will perform the following tasks:\n\n* Removing columns with large missingness\n* Data Partitioning\n* Imputation\n* Handle Outliers\n* Variable Scaling\n* Feature Creation\n* Feature Selection","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Data Dictionary\n\nCustomer churn data consists of demographic information, customer behavior, and marketing and advertising campaigns.\n\n- DemHomeOwner: Homeowner indicator\n- customerGender: Gender of the customer\n- LostCustomer: Indicator if the customer is lost (binary) **[TARGET COLUMN]**\n- regionPctCustomers: Percentage of customers in the region\n- numOfTotalReturns: Total number of returns\n- wksSinceLastPurch: Weeks since the last purchase\n- basktPurchCount12Month: Basket purchase count in the last 12 months\n- LastPurchaseAmount: Amount of last purchase\n- AvgPurchaseAmount12: Average purchase amount in the last 12 months\n- AvgPurchaseAmountTotal: Total average purchase amount\n- totalNumProdPurchased: Total number of products purchased\n- custInitiatedContacts: Customer-initiated contacts\n- customersales: Customer sales\n- techSupportEval: Evaluation of tech support\n- wksSinceFirstPurch: Weeks since the first purchase","outputs":[]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Input Data\n\n**We start from the SAS data set prepared in Data Engineering: CHURN.CUSTOMER_CHURN_ABT**\n\nIn case you have not followed previous steps, adapt and run the following code:\n","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":"/* Automatic macro-variable pointing to your storage mount path */\n/*\n%put &=WORKSPACE_PATH ;\n%let path=&WORKSPACE_PATH/sas-education/sas1 ;\n\nlibname churn \"&path/data/output\" ;\n*/","outputs":[{"items":[{"data":"[\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1718  /** LOG_START_INDICATOR **/\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1719  title;footnote;ods _all_ close;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1720  ods graphics on;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1721  ods html5(id=vscode) style=HTMLEncore options(bitmap_mode='inline' svg_mode='inline');\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"NOTE: Writing HTML5(VSCODE) Body file: sashtml91.htm\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1722  %let _SASPROGRAMFILE =\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1722! %nrquote(%nrstr(/workspaces/churnproject/sas-education/sas1/03_Addressing_the_Use_Case_with_the_SAS_Language/03_Machine_Learni\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1722! ng/02_Pre-Processing_Data.sasnb));\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1723  /* Automatic macro-variable pointing to your storage mount path */\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1724  /*\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1725  %put &=WORKSPACE_PATH ;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1726  %let path=&WORKSPACE_PATH/sas-education/sas1 ;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1727  \",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1728  libname churn \\\"&path/data/output\\\" ;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1729  */\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"65                                                         The SAS System                       Friday, October  3, 2025 06:45:00 PM\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"title\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"title\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1730  ;*';*\\\";*/;run;quit;ods html5(id=vscode) close;\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"1731  \",\n\t\t\"type\": \"source\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\t\"line\": \"\",\n\t\t\"type\": \"note\",\n\t\t\"version\": 1\n\t}\n]","mime":"application/vnd.sas.compute.log.lines"}]}]},{"kind":1,"language":"markdown","value":"## Removing Columns\n\n- birthdate (No direct predictive power.)\n- review_text and title (High cardinality and not performing text analytics.)\n- AvgPurchaseAmount12 (Strongly correlated column.)\n- intAdExposureCount12 and socialMediaAdCountAll (Columns used to create composite column.)","outputs":[]},{"kind":2,"language":"sas","value":" /* Drop columns: birthdate, unstructured data, a strongly correlated column, and columns used to create composite column */\ndata work.customer_churn_ml;\n    set churn.customer_churn_abt \n    (drop= birthdate \n           review_text title \n           AvgPurchaseAmount12 \n           intAdExposureCount12 socialMediaAdCountAll);\nrun;\n\ntitle1 \"Quick Listing of Variables Remaining in Churn Table\";\nproc contents order=varnum short;\nrun;\ntitle;","outputs":[{"items":[{"data":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\" xml:lang=\"en\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\"/>\n<meta content=\"SAS V.04.00\" name=\"generator\"/>\n<title>SAS Output</title>\n<style>\n/*<![CDATA[*/\n.body.c > table, .body.c > pre, .body.c div > table,\n.body.c div > pre, .body.c > table, .body.c > pre,\n.body.j > table, .body.j > pre, .body.j div > table,\n.body.j div > pre, .body.j > table, .body.j > pre,\n.body.c p.note, .body.c p.warning, .body.c p.error, .body.c p.fatal,\n.body.j p.note, .body.j p.warning, .body.j p.error, .body.j p.fatal,\n.body.c > table.layoutcontainer, .body.j > table.layoutcontainer { m